Apple=E2=80=99s iPad Event
------------------

From Bloomberg ( https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-05-07/apple-d=
ebuts-larger-ipad-air-in-device-s-first-update-since-2022 ) :

Apple Inc. unveiled a new artificial intelligence-focused iPad Pro and a la=
rger iPad Air, aiming to reinvigorate a tablet lineup that has languished o=
ver the past two years. At an online launch event Tuesday dubbed =E2=80=9CL=
et Loose,=E2=80=9D the company introduced the first redesigned version of t=
he iPad Pro since 2018. The new model is thinner, includes a crisper Ultra =
Retina XDR screen with OLED technology, and has a faster M4 chip that can h=
andle AI tasks. The new iPad Air looks like the prior version, but with a l=
arger screen-size option and the M2 processor. The new 13-inch iPad Pro has=
 a depth of 5.1 millimeters, which the company said makes it the thinnest A=
pple product ever. The bigger version is a quarter-pound lighter than its p=
redecessor, while the 11-inch model weighs under one pound.

The unveiling ends Apple=E2=80=99s longest drought in new iPad releases sin=
ce co-founder Steve Jobs first introduced the device in 2010. The lineup wa=
s previously updated October 2022, when Apple added a faster chip to the iP=
ad Pro and rolled out a redesigned low-end model. Apple is looking to pull =
the iPad out of a severe slump. The device=E2=80=99s sales were particularl=
y weak last quarter, when they plunged 17% and missed analysts=E2=80=99 est=
imates, but Apple predicted that iPad revenue would rebound in the current =
period.

The most notable technical change to the iPad was the M4 chip in the iPad P=
ro; at first glance this might seem like a big surprise given that the M3 o=
nly came out last fall, and was, like every M-series chip before it, based =
on an iPhone chip that came first (the A17 Pro, in this case). Moreover, ne=
w M3-based MacBooks Air just launched two months ago, so why doesn=E2=80=99=
t the iPad Pro have an M3?

The answer =E2=80=94 contra Apple=E2=80=99s PR push to insinuate that AI is=
 the driver =E2=80=94 is something I wrote about last fall ( https://strate=
chery.com/2023/china-chips-and-moores-law/?access_token=3DeyJhbGciOiJSUzI1N=
iIsImtpZCI6InN0cmF0ZWNoZXJ5LnBhc3Nwb3J0Lm9ubGluZSIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJhdWQ=
iOiJzdHJhdGVjaGVyeS5wYXNzcG9ydC5vbmxpbmUiLCJhenAiOiJIS0xjUzREd1Nod1AyWURLYm=
ZQV00xIiwiZW50Ijp7InVyaSI6WyJodHRwczovL3N0cmF0ZWNoZXJ5LmNvbS8yMDIzL2NoaW5hL=
WNoaXBzLWFuZC1tb29yZXMtbGF3LyJdfSwiZXhwIjoxNzE3NzY2ODQ1LCJpYXQiOjE3MTUxNzQ4=
NDUsImlzcyI6Imh0dHBzOi8vYXBpLnBhc3Nwb3J0Lm9ubGluZS9vYXV0aCIsInNjb3BlIjoiZmV=
lZDpyZWFkIGFydGljbGU6cmVhZCBhc3NldDpyZWFkIGNhdGVnb3J5OnJlYWQgZW50aXRsZW1lbn=
RzIiwic3ViIjoiUnNldVlFOGpnSGVQcFdKZjFmQWI0QyIsInVzZSI6ImFjY2VzcyJ9.G96lNOXp=
S-TcauQK6wnGUPkePI_PIGTu7W_R7BWPbzF_S964Chd3aYUEInaqOEhYpKyjbVTikn4tbDrJbp-=
6AqvorlQA8jxrLs6PJIAEbSvIGULQezCsQsdlWm6h4aZ4p5Fakfm95hLbQoQXGalVPf9UMW09VB=
FzwrxwnEpTU9QFcuxGl3FGcg65lnzJWQ4-sRdqP9jn8ki-mSh-YRfb_TwlTp0Au2kdYlQKnSBvj=
x8VUpwePJvxZfPNmK-f2SHKdrzGyBPOdHbYtPQ3g7zMTQlOrhWxYJ371NuIzCVRRKSXemAejjRz=
fFh5Ff-Vn9ohb_QFIjs_soayABqweR-dWw ) : the A17 Pro and M3 are based on TSMC=
=E2=80=99s first 3nm process (N3B) which ended up being a dead-end as far a=
s development goes. From WikiChip Fuse ( https://fuse.wikichip.org/news/704=
8/n3e-replaces-n3-comes-in-many-flavors/ ) back in 2022:

The N3 node is weird. It is TSMC=E2=80=99s first 3-nanometer class process =
technology, but it won=E2=80=99t be the mainstream node everyone will utili=
ze. In fact, it appears to be a one-off node that the company abandoned som=
etimes prior to rollout. It looks as if TSMC engineers encounter some roadb=
locks along the way and decided to change things mid-way. We say all of thi=
s because TSMC moved on to a whole different node this year called =E2=80=
=9CN3E=E2=80=9D which we discuss below. Most of the messaging at the Techno=
logy Symposium was about N3E with the original N3 node getting just a brief=
 pass-by mention. The big takeaway here is that N3E is a very different nod=
e from N3. While the nitty-gritty node details have not been disclosed, at =
a high-level it has different PPAs along with what the company claims are =
=E2=80=9Cvery different=E2=80=9D design rules intended to improve yield. Th=
e result of this is that N3E will not offer any direct migration path from =
N3, making N3 sort of a dead-end node for designers which is why TSMC expec=
ts most customers to utilize N3E instead. So why N3 exist at all? The easie=
st explanation is to satisfy customers=E2=80=99 commitment to those early t=
echnology adopters. Long term, the initial N3 node will likely fade into ob=
scurity.

In short, Apple already waited a year longer than they wanted to for N3; th=
ey weren=E2=80=99t going to wait another year once TSMC decided to rework t=
heir fundamental approach to 3nm, which is why TSMC pushed forward with a p=
rocess that had lower yields and an unclear path to further optimizations (=
this was part of the 3nm issues I referenced yesterday ( https://stratecher=
y.com/2024/tsmc-earnings-tsmcs-pricing-mistake-intel-v-tsmc/?access_token=
=3DeyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6InN0cmF0ZWNoZXJ5LnBhc3Nwb3J0Lm9ubGluZSIsInR5=
cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJhdWQiOiJzdHJhdGVjaGVyeS5wYXNzcG9ydC5vbmxpbmUiLCJhenAiOiJIS0=
xjUzREd1Nod1AyWURLYmZQV00xIiwiZW50Ijp7InVyaSI6WyJodHRwczovL3N0cmF0ZWNoZXJ5L=
mNvbS8yMDI0L3RzbWMtZWFybmluZ3MtdHNtY3MtcHJpY2luZy1taXN0YWtlLWludGVsLXYtdHNt=
Yy8iXX0sImV4cCI6MTcxNzc2Njg0NSwiaWF0IjoxNzE1MTc0ODQ1LCJpc3MiOiJodHRwczovL2F=
waS5wYXNzcG9ydC5vbmxpbmUvb2F1dGgiLCJzY29wZSI6ImZlZWQ6cmVhZCBhcnRpY2xlOnJlYW=
QgYXNzZXQ6cmVhZCBjYXRlZ29yeTpyZWFkIGVudGl0bGVtZW50cyIsInN1YiI6IlJzZXVZRThqZ=
0hlUHBXSmYxZkFiNEMiLCJ1c2UiOiJhY2Nlc3MifQ.NiUPqcbR7-x9hsxrL4g2j6pMdrQFHMPCu=
OsSBWTWAc31Xl8anLwbL_xOrQfz5zDR_MdUreWfx7S9PRsLBE2QtaIbX2vwgGGbpcjd8DamopxD=
_GkjGIcj8Q29tD1ndkp0hmZXjNL7u0J0GkqbjLLFe2TVQmY0WG7AErhNkypxOiUxRJDzXiAFQih=
TxcXwTPiWUrv5zG16On_zUQuFWBQL0if5GBNfCpngSGeVgUlxw0aYRT5-sYiR1_3QWai8pdqWsU=
F_P_hPd_GfZ0oed59mreIQypTPaw7PLfGWz-r3F8ILbBV4J6kkhmGZCobH13TzkOBgLpduJ3xtG=
HcQwh2Apw ) ) so that Apple could have the aforementioned A17 Pro and M3 ch=
ip. At the same time, neither Apple nor TSMC want that line to run forever,=
 and given the slower upgrade cycle for iPads, it makes a lot of sense to j=
ump forward to TSMC=E2=80=99s newer and more scalable N3E node.

So why the iPad Pro and not the MacBook Airs? I assume it simply comes down=
 to volume =E2=80=94 there probably aren=E2=80=99t enough M4 chips for Appl=
e=E2=80=99s most popular computer line, whereas I assume that iPads Pro sel=
l in much smaller volume =E2=80=94 and the fact that Apple will almost cert=
ainly refresh the MacBooks Air sooner rather than later. My bet would be so=
me time in the fall, after the next iPhone chip (which, by the way, may, fo=
r the first time in a while, go into both iPhones Pro and regular iPhones; =
I don=E2=80=99t expect the A17 Pro to drop down to the base model).

The Peaceful iPad
-----------------

Back in 2020, on the occasion of the iPad=E2=80=99s 10th anniversary, I wro=
te an Article entitled The Tragic iPad ( https://stratechery.com/2020/the-i=
pad-at-10-the-ipad-disappointment-ipads-missing-ecosystem/?access_token=3De=
yJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6InN0cmF0ZWNoZXJ5LnBhc3Nwb3J0Lm9ubGluZSIsInR5cCI6=
