hOaVFq9euycV1m4pyAiQGJ2lb1llAJIb2x-YfpEk802s3RNj6FSQpHtLyTiBfA1bkQumPvrTqfw=
GcABnwiM3JlCKdCZ9CITZKlrfRhwdPogaZThPJSAAJhUfe74OUVCTp18j96r660ne-UTq4oSbk2=
T5t-v_0V_UgJWxKHFRq1LJGcuzlG4XhTwNPDmQWPPBNjk-D5EeB5lPtx4D5Q3DYyzzcaeWZ6WS1=
0rwXIXatHAgvFZXRWTRvnsvPV37lghF2u7NL0B1BBw ) : that the App Store=E2=80=99s=
 restrictions on business models prevented the emergence of truly innovativ=
e applications that would make the iPad into something more than a portable=
 TV or an extremely frustrating Mac-replacement, and concluded:

To be fair, would that we all could =E2=80=9Cfail=E2=80=9D like the iPad; i=
t was a $21 billion business last fiscal year, nearly as much as the Mac=E2=
=80=99s $26 billion. That, though, is why I did not call it a failure: the =
tragedy of the iPad is not that it flopped, it is that it never did, and li=
kely never will, reach that potential so clearly seen ten years ago.

Four years on, and I=E2=80=99m ready to throw in the towel on this take: th=
e iPad is what it is, and I=E2=80=99m at peace with that =E2=80=94 which ra=
ises the question of what is it?

*A Personal TV:* If you visit LG=E2=80=99s website ( https://www.lg.com/us/=
tvs ) they have a whole host of models ranging from top-of-the-line multi-t=
housand-dollar OLED TVs down to basic few-hundred-dollar LED TVs; all of th=
ese TVs show the same content, but the quality of the screens varies signif=
icantly, even amongst models that have the same resolution. So it is with t=
he iPad line:

iPad iPad Air iPad Pro Resolution Retina Retina Retina Type Tandem OLED LED=
 LED Brightness 1000 nits 600 nits 500 nits HDR max 1600 nits N/A N/A Color=
 gamut P3 P3 sRGB Laminated Yes Yes No Antireflective Yes Yes No Price $1,2=
99 $799 $349

This is a pretty straightforward product lineup with basically the same seg=
mentation you might encounter when shopping for a TV for your living room; =
to that end, that new Tandem OLED screen was one of the biggest and most im=
portant features of the presentation.

*A Digital Canvas:* The most important addition Apple has made to the iPad =
over the last 14 years was not, as I once might have expected, subscription=
 pricing in the App Store; rather it was the Apple Pencil. What is so impor=
tant about the Apple Pencil (from a business perspective) is that it gives =
the iPad capabilities that don=E2=80=99t exist in any Apple device (and are=
 very much top-of-the-line in terms of a portable artistic studio, at least=
 according to my also-Wacom-tablet-owning daughter). This is the true =E2=
=80=9Ccreative=E2=80=9D story for the iPad: with an Apple Pencil you can do=
 things you just can=E2=80=99t do on any other Apple device.

*A Simple Computer:* From what I=E2=80=99ve seen there are three primary co=
nstituencies for the iPad-as-computer: children, retirees, and executives. =
These use cases are where the iPad=E2=80=99s iPhone roots work well. You ca=
n check your email, view photos, review documents, etc., all in an easy-to-=
carry device that doubles as personal entertainment on the couch, in the be=
d, or on a plane. Anyone that needs or wants to do more than that, though, =
is better served by a Mac (and I continue to maintain that =E2=80=9Cmulti-t=
asking=E2=80=9D has made the iPad worse for all of the above use cases).

These obviously aren=E2=80=99t the only things people use iPads for =E2=80=
=94 gaming and reading are two other obvious use cases =E2=80=94 but the re=
ason I highlight these three is that they give the iPad a reason to exist i=
ndependent of any other devices; an iPad is simply better than an iPhone or=
 a Mac at these specific use cases. No, they don=E2=80=99t represent the en=
tirely new way of creating content that I envisioned, but I have to admit I=
 never came up with any specific ideas myself that truly improved on the WI=
MP interface native to the Mac.

More pertinently, my takeaway from this presentation is that Apple has come=
 to a similar conclusion: in addition to the screen the other big feature w=
as the new Apple Pencil Pro. Yes, there were new versions of Final Cut and =
Logic for iPad, but I=E2=80=99m not sold on either being competitive with w=
hat you can do on a Mac =E2=80=94 but I=E2=80=99m glad the company is still=
 experimenting. Indeed, the only part of the presentation that felt out of =
place was in fact the M4: the technical reason why it is in the iPad is int=
eresting; the actual utility of it for what iPads are actually used for is =
confusing.

As an analogy, there=E2=80=99s a reason why Apple doesn=E2=80=99t spend muc=
h time talking about the processor for the Apple Watch: after a couple of y=
ears of exploration the company realized the primary use cases were health-=
and-fitness and and notifications; to the extent a new processor matters it=
 is because of increased efficiency, and, well, that was in fact the point =
they made most vociferously about the M4. If that helped make that incredib=
ly sexy thin personal TV possible then that=E2=80=99s fine by me.

