Disney and other media companies were not necessarily a contestant in this =
fight, but they were losers: when Input1 was a cable box there was a barrie=
r to entry, and the optimal strategy was to monopolize as many channels as =
possible; there is no barrier to entry for apps, which means the optimal st=
rategy is to put all of your resources behind one app, not splitting your c=
ontent up across multiple apps. In other words, when the cable bundle was t=
ightly wound, there was freedom for Disney to spread out; now that everythi=
ng is a marketplace fighting for a spot on the home screen, Disney is findi=
ng it optimal to bundle itself to the greatest extent possible.

